#note INFERE is a lot more points, but there really aren't a lot of good tiles left in the bag, which puts a premium on keeping a good leave. I picked RIMU instead of RAGI in order to keep row 13 open, because my bingos won't always go down on row 2 or 3. Indeed, RIMU improves my bingo % by about 5%, but at the cost of opening column A for scoring plays, which makes RAGI preferable. Another choice is FENI keeping EIRRS for 13 more. Considering the game situation, Austin has been grooming his rack for 3 turns and just played off ADI, suggesting a potent leave - so I felt urgency to bingo first before he blocks up rows 2 and 3. In reality his leave after KAID was much weaker than I would've thought. All in all I might pick FENI.
